{
  "texts": [
    "Model-oriented stage, 4.",
    "Operation stage.",
    "In scenarios in which we want to train ML/DL models with data from different clients or data owners, the most intuitive and widely applied approach is the centralized one.",
    "The idea is to centralize all available data in a single location to train the model using all the data stored.",
    "Thus, the trained model will have better generalizability, as it has been trained with more data from different data owners (AbdulRahman et al. 2020)."
  ]
}